item.title: CVE-2020-29510|2024-09-16T16:48:42.611Z -- golang -- go
item.description: The encoding/xml package in Go versions 1.15 and earlier does not correctly preserve the semantics of directives during tokenization round-trips, which allows an attacker to craft inputs that behave in conflicting ways during different stages of processing in affected downstream applications.
